"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">a)</span><span style=\" font-family:\'Times New Roman\'; font-size:7pt;\">   </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">f = 4Khz</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><img src=\"file:///C:/Users/Habtamu/AppData/Local/Packages/oice_16_974fa576_32c1d314_2c2d/AC/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_image008.png\" width=\"57\" height=\"46\" /><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">  </span><img src=\"file:///C:/Users/Habtamu/AppData/Local/Packages/oice_16_974fa576_32c1d314_2c2d/AC/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_image010.png\" width=\"65\" height=\"43\" /><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 0.25msec</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">During the sweep time of 0.5 msec the input signal will go through 2 cycles.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">b)</span><span style=\" font-family:\'Times New Roman\'; font-size:7pt;\">  </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">  f = 8KHz</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><img src=\"file:///C:/Users/Habtamu/AppData/Local/Packages/oice_16_974fa576_32c1d314_2c2d/AC/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_image008.png\" width=\"57\" height=\"46\" /><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">  </span><img src=\"file:///C:/Users/Habtamu/AppData/Local/Packages/oice_16_974fa576_32c1d314_2c2d/AC/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_image012.png\" width=\"65\" height=\"43\" /><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 0.125msec</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">c)</span><span style=\" font-family:\'Times New Roman\'; font-size:7pt;\">    </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">  f = 1khz</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><img src=\"file:///C:/Users/Habtamu/AppData/Local/Packages/oice_16_974fa576_32c1d314_2c2d/AC/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_image008.png\" width=\"57\" height=\"46\" /><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">  </span><img src=\"file:///C:/Users/Habtamu/AppData/Local/Packages/oice_16_974fa576_32c1d314_2c2d/AC/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_image014.png\" width=\"65\" height=\"43\" /><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 1msec</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">In 0.5msec, the input signal will go through ½ a cycle.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">The usual method of synchronizing the input signal uses to trigger the sweep generator so that the rate of the sweep signal is looked or synchronized ot the input signal, which is called internal synchronization.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Line Synchronization </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">Sometimes triggering is provided from the main power line. This mode is useful for observing waveform which bar a fixed relationship to the line frequency.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">External mode of synchronization</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> this involves the application of a completely new triggering signal from the applied to the input terminals. It is useful to the measurement of the phase difference between the waveform.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Power supplies </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">The oscilloscope has two power supplies to provide dc voltage for its various subassemblies. The high power supply 10 Kv drives the CRT and the low voltage power supply 400v provides power for the amplifiers and triggering circuitry.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Application </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">Among the several uses of the oscilloscope are measurement of voltage, frequency and phase shift.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Voltage measurement </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">To measure the ac component of a signal, display the wave form over the larger portion of the screen. Multiply the number of centimeters between the desired points by the setting of the amplitude control. Make sure that the variable control is in the calibrated position.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">To measure the dc level of a signal, set the input switch of the signal connector to the ground position. Position the trace to a line appropriate for the polarity and amplitude of the signal to be measured. Once this reference line has been restablished do not change this position control. Taking a certain point on the display, the dc value of the signal will be the vertical shift of this point when the input switch is changed between its ac and dc positions.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Time measurement </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">To measure the time interval between two points on a signal waveform, multiply the distance between the point in centimeter by the setting of the sweep time/cm in the calibrated position.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Phase shift measurement </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">Among the several methods used we will look at the following two techniques.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00007f;\">I)</span><span style=\" font-family:\'Times New Roman\'; font-size:7pt; color:#00007f;\">                  </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Time interval measurement:</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt; color:#00007f;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">Measure the distance between two corresponding points on the input and output waveform of the phase shifting circuit (assuming a dual trace oscilloscope is used) in centimeters. Dividing this amount by the distance of one period and multiplying the result by 360 degree gives the phase shift in degrees between the signal under measurement.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00007f;\">II)</span><span style=\" font-family:\'Times New Roman\'; font-size:7pt; color:#00007f;\">               </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00007f;\">Lissajous pattern measurement:</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt; color:#00007f;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">When two signals of the same frequency are applied separately to the vertical and horizontal plates of the CRO, the resulting lissajous pattern is an ellipse is which is an ellipse which has interesting properties leading in the phase shift determination.</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> </span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">Normally the reference signal is applied to the horizontal amplifier. Let this signal be expressed by</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">X(t) = X cos wt</span><span style=\" font-size:8pt;\"> </span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">And the signal applied to the vertical amplifier By </span></p>\n"
